'''''Jedi Apprentice: The Evil Experiment''''' is a [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] junior novel written by [[Jude Watson]]. It is the twelfth volume of the ''[[Star Wars: Jedi Apprentice]]'' series, following [[Jedi Apprentice: The Deadly Hunter|''The Deadly Hunter'']] and preceding [[Jedi Apprentice: The Dangerous Rescue|''The Dangerous Rescue'']]. It was published in paperback by [[Scholastic]] in [[February]] [[2001]].

==Publisher's summary==
''An evil scientist is imprisoning and torturing Jedi to find the secret behind the Force. She taps their emotions, monitors their actions&hellip;and then drains them of their blood.''

''Qui-Gon Jinn is now her captive.''

''Obi-Wan Kenobi is desperately searching for his Master. Meanwhile, Qui-Gon must match wits with one of the most dangerous enemies he has ever encountered.''

''His survival depends on it.''

==Plot summary==
[[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan]] and [[Astri Oddo|Astri]] voyage to [[Sorrus]] to track down the mysterious [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] who has kidnapped [[Qui-Gon Jinn/Legends|Qui-Gon]]. Meanwhile, Qui-Gon weakens as [[Jenna Zan Arbor]] subjects him to experiments in her secret [[Laboratory/Legends|laboratory]] in an endeavor to understand the biological underpinnings of the [[The Force/Legends|Force]].

